  Texas COVID-19 Vaccine Tracker





  The reach of COVID-19 on Texas and the world has been devastating. As our state joins a global effort to put coronavirus into our past, we are tracking the Texas vaccine roll-out as it unfolds in real-time.
  Texas has 22,421,178 people above the age of 16 who at some point will be eligible for a vaccine. As of Mar 27, 2021, the state has:


   | Fully Vaccinated: 3,683,989 people or 16% of the population 16+  | Vaccinated w/ At Least One Dose: 7,043,729 people or 31% of the population 16+  | Administered: 34,173 doses in one day on Mar 27, 2021 or 0.15% of the population 16+  | A 7-Day Average of 154,198 administered per day or 0.69% of the population 16+



